<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-40-0029 </DOCNO><TEXT>Discusses development of industrial robots used in plants manufacturingequipment for underground coal mines. Standard design of first and secondgeneration robots is comparatively evaluated. Design of manipulatorsand factors that influence their reliability, accuracy and efficiencyare analyzed. Computerized control systems for robots as well as developmenttrends of advanced robots and manipulators are discussed. The followingproblems are reviewed: types of sensors, look and move systems, software(world modelling). Programming systems for new generations of robotsare discussed. 7 refs.</TEXT></DOC>